Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Drain the @mozzarella{1%ball} and squeeze out as much liquid as you can. Pat dry with #kitchen paper{}, then tear into small pieces.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, add the @diced chorizo{90%g} and sliced pepper and fry until just soft, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic, @chipotle paste{20%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and black beans, then fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1%carton} and the @sugar{1/2%tsp} for the sauce (see pantry for amount) through the bean mixture.

Reduce the heat to medium and simmer until thickened, ~{7-8%minutes}, then mash half of the beans using a #potato masher{} or the back of a #fork{}.

Once the sauce has thickened, lay the @plain taco tortillas{6} on a #board{} (3 per person). Reserve a quarter of the bean mixture for the topping, then spoon the remaining bean mixture down the centre of each, then roll them up to enclose the filling.

Drizzle a little oil over the bottom of an #ovenproof dish{}, then lay in the wraps. Pack them snugly, side by side, with the folded edge underneath so they don't unroll. Top with the reserved bean mixture and mozzarella. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, add the @red wine vinegar{12%ml}, @sugar{1/4%tsp} and the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing (see pantry for amount). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix well.

Just before you're ready to serve, toss the @wild rocket{20%g} through the dressing.

When everything's ready, share your chipotle chorizo enchiladas between your plates. Serve the rocket salad alongside. Enjoy!

> This Chipotle Chorizo and Black Bean Enchiladas is bursting full of flavours and makes the perfect dinner night option from HelloFresh. Cook up a fresh start!